## Clone a specific branch########### Helps when you have clone issue due to sub module error in master #########
## You can change the submodule settings (.gitmodules file) and clone the specific brnach ##########

git clone --recurse-submodules -b test git@github.com:org/repo.git

### Make sure you changed the sub module path in .gitmodules file ###
### This will merge the submodule to their latest commit ###

git submodule update --remote --merge

git add .
git commit -m "commit message"
git push

-------Rebase and merge---------
git pull --rebase [on local branch]
git checkout master
git pull --rebase
git checkout rel/11.x.x
git checkout master
git merge origin/rel/11.x.x  â†’ This will merge the rel/11.x.x of remote repo to the checked in local branch


Git checkout rel/11.x.x
 Git show  {it shows the sha of the last commit}
 Git tag 11.x.x-b1234  -m "Message"	{Where b is the constant for build and 1234 is the 4 digit     build number in the release email}
 Git push --tags

 Git checkout master
 Git branch -D rel/11.x.x

